Sanditi AI Virtual Try-On

An AI-powered virtual try-on system that enables realistic garment swapping on human images using multimodal generative models.

Built for fashion brands, designers, and ecommerce platforms to reduce sampling costs and enhance digital merchandising workflows.

⸻

🚀 Features
	•	👕 AI Virtual Try-On
	•	Upload a model image and garment image
	•	Automatically swaps clothing with high realism
	•	Preserves face, pose, and identity
	•	🎨 Background / Moment Generation
	•	Replace backgrounds using text prompts
	•	Keeps subject and outfit unchanged
	•	Ideal for campaign and lifestyle visuals
	•	🛍️ AI Styling Assistant
	•	Generates styling suggestions (jewelry, footwear, handbags)
	•	Clean, brand-free recommendations
	•	Structured JSON output
	•	⚡ Smart Model Routing
	•	Premium model for try-on accuracy
	•	Cost-efficient model for background edits
	•	🔁 Retry System
	•	Handles API overload (503 errors)
	•	Improves reliability in production

⸻

💼 Real-World Usage

This system is actively used in a production workflow for apparel development and digital sampling, helping reduce physical sampling costs and accelerate design decisions.

⸻

🧠 How It Works

Mode 1: Virtual Try-On
	•	Input: user image + garment image
	•	Output: realistic clothing swap

Mode 2: Background Generation
	•	Input: user image + text prompt
	•	Output: same person in a new environment

⸻

🛠 Tech Stack
	•	Node.js
	•	Express.js
	•	Multer
	•	Google Generative AI (Gemini)
	•	CORS

⸻

📡 API Endpoint

POST /api/try-on

Form Data:
	•	userImage (required)
	•	garmentImage (required for try-on)
	•	backgroundPrompt (optional)

🔧 Installation
git clone https://github.com/sandittiedit/sanditi-tryon
cd sanditi-tryon
npm install

Create .env file:
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

Run:
node server.js

📦 Response
{
  "imageBase64": "...",
  "style_advice": "..."
}

